# Website Enricher

Runs **in parallel** with the main VikiLeads scraper. Polls `leads.jsonl` every
3 seconds for rows where `Website` is empty, enriches them via Gemini + DeepSeek,
and writes the confirmed domain back into the file.

## Setup

### 1. Start the dedicated Chrome instance (once, before anything)

```bat
"C:\Program Files\Google\Chrome\Application\chrome.exe" ^
  --remote-debugging-port=9224 ^
  --user-data-dir="C:\website_enricher"
```

Sign into your Google account so Gemini is accessible.

### 2. Add DeepSeek key to `.env` (project root)

```
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
```

### 3. Start the main scraper job as normal

```bat
node server.js
```

### 4. In a second terminal, start the enricher pointing at the same job folder

```bat
node website-enricher/enricher.js --dir "C:\Users\Hassan\Downloads\vikileads_updated\data\<jobid>"
```

The enricher auto-stops when it detects `job.done` (written by job-runner at completion)
and all remaining empty rows have been processed. Use `--watch` to keep it running
indefinitely.

## Flow

```
Every 3s:
  Read leads.jsonl
  ↓
  Find rows where Website is empty
  ↓
  Batch 5 at a time → Gemini (port 9224)
    "What is the official website domain of 'CompanyName'?"
  ↓
  Confirmed candidates → DeepSeek purifier
    "Does domain.com belong to CompanyName?"
  ↓
  Write confirmed domains back to leads.jsonl
  ↓
  Regenerate leads.csv + leads.xlsx
```

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `enricher.js` | Main watcher + orchestrator |
| `geminiScraper.js` | Playwright CDP connection to Gemini tab |
| `deepseekPurifier.js` | DeepSeek domain validation |